# <!-- Audit: I.6 (i6-compliance-artefacts) -->
# Forge — `.forge/.forge-dpa-declared` DPA declaration template
#
# Canonical attestation surface for adopters who declare T1 with
# ⚠️-T1 components in scope (Schrems II / CLOUD Act residual risk
# accepted under a DPA + SCC envelope).
#
# Format pinned by ADR-K3-002 (`.forge/changes/k3-demeter/design.md`).
# Format documented by `.forge/standards/global/data-stewardship-rules.md`
# § "DPA declaration semantics".
#
# Rule cross-reference :
# - K3-RULE-002    — fires when `compliance_tier=T1` carries ⚠️-T1
#                    components without a `.forge/.forge-dpa-declared`
#                    ledger present (severity High).
# - K3-RULE-002a   — staleness check : Demeter emits a Medium finding
#                    when `today − date > 13 months` (RGPD review cycle
#                    + 1 month grace).
#
# What Demeter parses :
#   The one-line attestation
#   `T1: <ISO-8601-date> <free-form-ref>` (mandatory trailing newline).
#
# What Demeter does NOT do (legal-domain work, out of K.3 scope per
# FR-K3-DEM-044) :
#   - parse DPA legal text ;
#   - verify Standard Contractual Clauses ;
#   - check signature authenticity ;
#   - inspect counterparty identity.
#
# The ledger format MIRRORS the J.8 `.forge/.forge-tier` pattern
# shipped by ADR-J8-006 verbatim. Per-project (not committed by
# default — adopters decide).
#
# ─── Instructions ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Copy this template to `.forge/.forge-dpa-declared` at the root
#    of your Forge project.
# 2. Replace the example line below with your attestation. The
#    `<free-form-ref>` field is a stable handle your legal team can
#    use to retrieve the underlying DPA document (Confluence page,
#    SharePoint folder, ticket id — adopter choice).
# 3. Re-attest at least every 13 months to avoid the K3-RULE-002a
#    staleness finding (RGPD Article 5(1)(e) review cadence + 1
#    month grace).
# 4. Commit the ledger to your project repo if your governance
#    allows ; otherwise keep it local + reproducible via your
#    secret-management surface.
#
# Example: T1: 2026-04-15 LegalOps-Confluence-DPA-2026-Q2
